20after%20the%20police%20had%20arrested%20an%20ED%20official%20in%20the%20state.%20On%20December%201%2C%20the%20state%20police%20arrested%20ED%20official%20Ankit%20Tiwari%2C%20alleging%20that%20he%20had%20been%20caught%20%E2%80%9Cred-handed%E2%80%9D%20while%20accepting%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2020%20lakh%20from%20a%20doctor%20in%20the%20Dindigul%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETiwari%20along%20with%20his%20team%20of%20ED%20officers%20had%20allegedly%20been%20threatening%20several%20people%20and%20receiving%20bribes%20in%20the%20name%20of%20closing%20their%20case%20at%20the%20ED%2C%20the%20police%20stated.%20DVAC%20officials%20caught%20him%20with%20Rs%2020%20lakh%20cash%20in%20Dindigul.%20DVAC%20also%20searched%20the%20ED%20Office%20in%20Madurai.%20Tiwari%20is%20still%20in%20jail%2C%20having%20been%20denied%20bail%20by%20both%20the%20trial%20court%20and%20the%20Madras%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2Fchennai%2Ftamil-nadu-police-register-case-against-ed-officials-for-preventing-dvac-investigators-from-discharging-their-duties%2Farticle67671891.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20fresh%20case%20filed%20by%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Police%20against%20in%20the%20ED%2C%20the%20police%20claim%20that%20the%20ED%20refused%20to%20allow%20DVAC%20officials%20to%20search%20Tiwari%E2%80%99s%20offices%20after%20his%20arrest%20on%20December%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20Madurai%20city%20police%20that%20the%20DVAC%20search%20team%20was%20prevented%20from%20entering%20the%20chamber%20of%20accused%20officer%20Ankit%20Tiwari%20for%20more%20than%20three%20hours.%20The%20Assistant%20Director%20informed%20that%20the%20Deputy%20Director%20was%20in%20Chennai%20and%20was%20air%20dashing%20to%20Madurai%20to%20approve%20the%20search.%20But%20he%20did%20not%20come%E2%80%A6%20we%20had%20to%20seek%20the%20assistance%20of%20the%20local%20police%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20search%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20senior%20DVAC%20official%20told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Hindu.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ED%20too%20claims%20to%20be%20probing%20both%20Tiwari%20as%20well%20as%20officers%20of%20the%20DVAC.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fed-vs-tn-cops-agency-shifts-case-to-delhi-hq%2Farticleshow%2F106276481.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20ED%20has%20moved%20this%20probe%20out%20of%20the%20state%20to%20its%20New%20Delhi%20headquarters.%20ED%20sources%20reportedly%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20this%20was%20because%20of%20fears%20of%20meddling%20from%20the%20local%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ED%20claims%20had%20previously%20filed%20a%20complaint%20against%20DVAC%20officers%20with%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Police%2C%20which%20did%20not%20register%20an%20FIR.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fbribery-case-tn-cops-ask-ed-officer-to-appear-at-police-station-on-dec-26-2824801%5C%22%3Emedia%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Beniwal%E2%80%99s%20complaints%20from%20December%202%20had%20accused%20the%20DVAC%20team%20of%20accessing%20sensitive%20case%20records%2C%20information%20and%20internal%20documents%20of%20the%20ED%20related%20to%20other%20cases%20which%20have%20no%20link%20with%20the%20alleged%20search%20case%2C%20and%20ransacking%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20entire%20office%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Police%20officers%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20they%20received%20no%20such%20complaint%20from%20the%20ED%20on%20that%20date.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20states%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20December%2016%2C%202023%2C%20a%20reminder%20letter%20requesting%20action%20was%20received%20by%20the%20DGP%E2%80%99s%20office%20wherein%20the%20original%20complaint%20was%20enclosed.%20The%20D