ased%20after%20the%20cops%20were%20convinced%20the%20passengers%20had%20boarded%20the%20flight%20out%20of%20free%20will%2C%20reports%20suggest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20lawyer%20said%20the%20judge%20was%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bresist%20media%20pressure%20in%20this%20case%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20led%20to%20their%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%20belonging%20to%20Romania's%20Legend%20Airlines%20landed%20in%20Mumbai%20early%20this%20morning%20with%20276%20passengers%20after%20a%20go-ahead%20from%20a%20French%20judge.%20It%20departed%20Vatry%20around%202%3A30%20pm%20(local%20time)%20and%20reached%20Mumbai%20just%20after%204%20am%20(IST).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20known%20exactly%20how%20many%20Indians%20are%20among%20the%20276%20passengers%20and%20what%20nationality%20are%20the%20other%20flyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nicaragua-bound%20Airbus%20A340%20was%20carrying%20303%20passengers%2C%20most%20of%20them%20Indians%2C%20when%20it%20reached%20Vatry%20airport%20near%20Paris%20last%20Friday.%20It%20was%20grounded%20on%20its%20arrival%20from%20Dubai%20for%20refuelling%20after%20an%20anonymous%20tip-off%20that%20the%20passengers%20could%20be%20potential%20trafficking%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrench%20authorities%20are%20still%20probing%20the%20case%20for%20immigration%20law%20violation%2C%20not%20human%20trafficking%20any%20more%2C%20reports%20suggest%20citing%20judicial%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENicaragua%20in%20central%20America%20is%20a%20popular%20destination%20for%20immigrants%20to%20cross%20into%20the%20US%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%2097%2C000%20Indians%20have%20tried%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20illegally%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202023%2C%20a%20whopping%2051.61%20percent%20jump%20from%20the%20previous%20year%20as%20per%20US%20official%20data.%20At%20least%2041%2C770%20of%20those%20Indians%20tried%20to%20cross%20the%20Mexican%20land%20border%20into%20the%20US%2C%20the%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Patrol%20(CBP)%2