iding%20among%20other%20groups%20in%20the%20state.%20Republican%20presidential%20candidates%20often%20struggle%20to%20win%20more%20than%2015%25%20of%20the%20Black%20vote%2C%20so%20if%20Trump%20eats%20into%20what%20has%20been%20Biden's%20most%20consistent%20base%20of%20support%2C%20it'll%20severely%20curtail%20the%20president's%20chances%20of%20winning%20the%20Peach%20State%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20voter%20mobilization%20will%20be%20key%20for%20Biden%20next%20year%20if%20he%20wants%20to%20win%20the%20state's%2016%20electoral%20votes%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227905%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Biden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6585eb3dcefc010bea26dc82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225271%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20pictured%20at%20the%20Red%20Butte%20Airfield%20in%20Coconino%20County%2C%20Arizona.%20The%20president%20hopes%20to%20capture%20the%20state's%2011%20electoral%20votes%20once%20again%20in%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJohn%20Locher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EWill%20Arizona's%20Latino%20voters%20come%20out%20for%20Biden%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%202020%20win%20in%20Arizona%20represented%20another%20major%20milestone%20for%20Democrats%20in%20the%20West%2C%20as%20the%20party's%20recent%20gains%20have%20been%20powered%20by%20the%20growing%20Latino%20vote%20in%20the%20region.%20It's%20a%20reason%20why%20Colorado%20and%20New%20Mexico%20have%20become%20so%20Democratic%20on%20the%20presidential%20level%2C%20while%20Nevada%20has%20more%20often%20than%20not%20trended%20Democratic%20in%20statewide%20races%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Biden%20did%20in%202020%20was%20something%20that%20Democrats%20had%20long%20aspired%20to%20do%20in%20Arizona%3A%20win%20populous%20Maricopa%20County%2C%20turn%20out%20Latino%20voters%2C%20and%20peel%20off%20enough%20suburban%20independents%20to%20capture%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was