news%2Fdense-fog-disrupts-flight-operations-at-delhi-and-hyderabad-airports-123122500312_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fdense-fog-disrupts-flight-operations-at-delhi-and-hyderabad-airports-123122500312_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lull%20in%20Highway%20Construction%20Expected%20in%20FY25%2C%20Flagship%20Highway%20Project%20Faces%206%20Year%20Delay%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F26130435%2F30501593928_465a2ee4cf_c-e1682494521102.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20construction%20of%20national%20highways%20is%20expected%20to%20slow%20down%20in%20FY25%20on%20account%20of%20decline%20in%20projects%20awarded%20during%20FY24.%20Projects%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20just%202%2C817%20km%20were%20awarded%20till%20November%202023%2C%20compared%20to%205%2C382%20km%20during%20the%20same%20period%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Flogistics%2Fa-slow-stretch-lies-ahead%2Farticle67669673.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%20(MoRTH)%20said%20that%20approvals%20need%20to%20be%20expedited%20for%20the%20revised%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20project%20or%20any%20alternative%20programme%20to%20meet%20the%20targeted%20awards%20for%20FY24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shortfall%20may%20worsen%20with%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20effect%20during%20January-March%202024.%20March%20typically%20sees%20a%20significant%20percentage%20of%20road%20project%20awards%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Flogistics%2Fa-slow-stretch-lies-ahead%2Farticle67669673.ece%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EICRA%2C%20a%20ratings%20agency%2C%20predicted%20a%20lower%20overall%20award%20in%20FY24%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20cutting%20its%20forecast%20to%207%2C000-7%2C500%20km%2C%20a%2040-43%25%20decline%20year-on-year.%20The%20delay%20in%20Cabinet%20approval%20for%20the%20revised%20cost%20of%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20has%20also%20slowed%20the%20project%20awarding%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBreaking%20down%20the%20awarding%20process%2C%20Modani%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Flogistics%2Fa-slow-stretch-lies-ahead%2Farticle67669673.ece%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20award%2C%20say%2C%20in%20July%2C%20August%20or%20September%2C%20then%20financial%20closure%20and%20so%20on%20happen%20six%20months%20down%20the%20line%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20appointed%20date.%20So%2C%20it%20generally%20takes%208-9%20months%20for%20work%20to%20begin%20after%20the%20awarding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccordingly%2C%20FY24%20will%20not%20be%20impacted%20because%20most%20projects%20are%20underway%20at%20a%20comfortable%20clip.%20However%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20slowdown%20in%20awarding%20during%20the%20current%20fiscal%2C%20then%20execution%20will%20be%20impacted%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20FY25%20and%2C%20subsequently%2C%20FY26%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ICRA%2C%20there%20is%20a%20preference%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98engineering%2C%20procurement%2C%20and%20construction%E2%80%99%20(EPC)%20route%20in%20road%20project%20awards%2C%20with%20a%20gradual%20shift%20towards%20%E2%80%98build%2C%20operate%20and%20transfer%E2%80%99%20(BOT)-toll%20projects%20which%20require%20less%20funding%20support%20from%20the%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBharatmala%20Phase-I%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20also%20decided%20to%20extend%20the%20completion%20deadline%20for%20the%20flagship%20highway%20development%20project%2C%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%2C%20from%202022%20to%202027-28.%20The%20six-year%20delay%20from%20the%20original%20schedule%20is%20primarily%20driven%20by%20a%20more%20than%20100%25%20increase%20in%20the%20estimated%20cost%20of%20the%20project%20which%20is%20now%20standing%20at%20nearly%20Rs%2011%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20ministry%20of%20road%20transport%20and%20highways%E2%80%99%20endeavour%20to%20award%20all%20projects%20on%20completion%20of%20land%20acquisition%20and%20obtaining%20all%20clearances%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024-25%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20length%20of%2034%2C800%20km%2C%20approximately%2076%25%2C%20or%2026%2C418%20km%2C%20of%20highway%20stretches%20have%20been%20awarded%20so%20far.%20Despite%20this%20progress%2C%20the%20first%20eight%20months%20of%20the%20current%20financial%20year%20have%20seen%20only%20102%20km%20of%20projects%20under%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20being%20awarded%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pace%20of%20awarding%20projects%20is%20expected%20to%20further%20slow%20down%20until%20the%20Cabinet%20Committee%20on%20Economic%20Affairs%20(CCEA)%20sanctions%20the%20revised%20cost%20of%20the%20project.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20has%20imposed%20restrictions%2C%20barring%20the%20highways%20ministry%20from%20creating%20any%20fresh%20liability%20under%20the%20project%20until%20CCEA%20approval%20is%20secured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20extended%20completion%20deadline%20set%20for%202027-28%2C%20only%2042%25%2C%20or%2015%2C045%20km%2C%20of%20the%20project%20had%20been%20completed%20as%20of%20November-end%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cabinet%20committee%20initially%20approved%20the%20first%20phase%20in%202017%2C%20estimating%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%205.35%20trillion.%20However%2C%20the%20sanctioned%20cost%20of%20awarded%20projects%20has%20surpassed%20Rs%208.5%20trillion%2C%20prompting%20the%20Public%20Investment%20Board%20to%20appraise%20the%20revised%20cost%20of%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20at%20Rs%2010.95%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703491345000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F26130435%2F30501593928_465a2ee4cf_c-e1682494521102.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flull-in-highway-construction-expected-in-fy25-flagship-highway-projected-faces-6-year-delay%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20shortfall%20may%20worsen%20with%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20effect%20during%20January-March%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flull-in-highway-construction-expected-in-fy25-flagship-highway-projected-faces-6-year-delay%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Serbia%20protests%3A%20Demonstrators%20throw%20rocks%20at%20Belgrade%20City%20Hall%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703489226000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F94D8%2Fproduction%2F_132140183_p0h1jgt9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67819176%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Riot%20police%20used%20tear%20gas%20to%20disperse%20crowds%20protesting%20at%20alleged%20fraud%20in%20last%20week's%20general%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-europe-67819176%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Has%20BJP%20MP%2C%20Ex-WFI%20Head%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%20Been%20Brought%20Down%20a%20Peg%20or%20Two%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F25124341%2FGA1OyoaXkAIKcph.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20meeting%20between%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%2C%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20MP%20and%20former%20president%20of%20the%20Wrestling%20Federation%20of%20India%2C%20and%20party%20president%20J.P.%20Nadda%20suggests%20Singh%20may%20have%20become%20more%20powerful%20in%20the%20scheme%20of%20things%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20emerged%20saying%20he%20has%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20to%20do%20with%20wrestling%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20and%20drew%20attention%20to%20how%20he%20still%20reigned%20supreme%20in%20the%20party.%20He%20said%20he%20had%20bigger%20tasks%20to%20accomplish%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%202024%20general%20election.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1738848801140482326%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EPTI%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CWFI%20elections%20were%20held%20on%20SC%20%5BSupreme%20Court%5D%20directions.%20Further%2C%20Sanjay%20Singh%20is%20not%20my%20relative.%20To%20resume%20the%20sports%20activities%20and%20not%20waste%20a%20year%20of%20young%20wrestlers%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20to%20conduct%20the%20games%20in%20Nandini%20Nagar.%20Now%2C%20I%20do%20not%20have%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20wrestling%20and%20have%20to%20look%20into%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20that%20are%20approaching.%20Whatever%20decision%20has%20to%20be%20taken%20will%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20new%20federation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20sport%20now.%20I%20have%20other%20responsibilities%20to%20focus%20now.%20I%20will%20be%20away%20from%20the%20politics%20of%20this%20sport%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fsanjay-singh-not-my-relative-says-brij-bhushan-on-suspension-of-wfi-backs-announcement-of-u-15-u-20-nationals-2823897%5C%22%3Ewrites%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20would%20suggest%20he%20has%20just%20being%20taken%20off%20from%20wrestling%2C%20as%20the%20public%20attention%20as%20well%20as%20visible%20annoyance%20of%20the%20influential%20Jat%20community%20in%20Haryana%20was%20getting%20hard%20to%20avoid.%20But%20B.B.S.%20Singh%20remains%20central%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20plans%20in%20the%20future%20and%20it%20has%20not%20been%20ruled%20out%20by%20the%20party%20that%20he%20may%20be%20accommodated%20in%20a%20more%20powerful%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20previously%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20Police%20(directly%20under%20the%20control%20of%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah)%20has%20never%20really%20moved%20on%20Singh%3B%20it%20took%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20to%20even%20get%20an%20FIR%20filed.%20The%20Delhi%20Police%20told%20a%20court%20in%20September%20that%20the%20BJP%20MP%20had%20%E2%80%9Coutraged%20the%20modesty%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20women%20wrestlers.%20This%20was%20when%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Rouse%20Avenue%20court%20was%20hearing%20the%20case%20on%20framing%20of%20charges%20against%20him%20after%20the%C2%A0chargesheet%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20sexual%20harassment%20case%C2%A0filed%20by%20six%20women%20wrestlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw%2Fstory%2Fbrij-bhushan-singh-harassed-wrestlers-at-every-opportunity-delhi-police-to-court-2439705-2023-09-24%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20Additional%20Public%20Prosecutor%20Atul%20Srivastava%2C%20representing%20the%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20WFI%20chief%20%E2%80%9Cknew%20what%20he%20was%20doing%E2%80%9D%20and%20his%20intention%20was%20to%20outrage%20the%20modesty%20of%20the%20wrestlers.%20He%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20are%20three%20types%20of%20evidence%20against%20Singh%20which%20are%20enough%20to%20frame%20charges.%20These%20include%20a%20written%20complaint%20and%20two%20recorded%20statements%20under%20Sections%20161%20(examination%20of%20witnesses%20by%20the%20police)%20and%20164%20(statements%20recorded%20by%20a%20magistrate)%20under%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC).%20Srivastava%20is%20reported%20to%20have%20said%20the%20court%20is%20within%20its%20jurisdiction%20to%20frame%20charges%20against%20Singh.%20He%20also%20countered%20the%20argument%20made%20by%20the%20WFI%20chief%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20that%20sanction%20under%20Section%20188%20of%20the%20CrPC%20is%20required%20for%20cases%20that%20took%20place%20outside%20India.%20But%20Singh%20continued%20to%20show%20growing%20impunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20while%20speaking%20to%20meritorious%20students%20in%20his%20constituency%20of%20Gonda%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20how%20he%20had%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Futtar-pradesh%2Fdabang-since-childhood-failed-twice-in-class-8-says-brijbhushan-sharan-singh-while-felicitating-meritorious-students-2776476%5C%22%3Ethat%20he%20had%20been%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Edabang%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20(muscleman)%20since%20his%20childhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20he%20had%2C%20after%20failing%20twice%20in%20the%208th%20standard%2C%20one%20of%20his%20classmates%20write%20his%20answer%20sheets%20by%20threatening%20to%20%E2%80%98break%E2%80%99%20his%20bones%20if%20he%20(the%20classmate)%20refused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20election%20of%20the%20new%20president%2C%20scenes%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestatesman.com%2Findia%2Fdabdaba-tha-dabdaba-rahega-says-brij-bhushan-singh-after-close-aide-wins-wfi-poll-1503251972.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Edab%20daba%20thaa%2C%20dab%20daba%20rahega%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(we%20have%20had%20control%2C%20will%20retain%20control)%E2%80%9D%20emerged%2C%20with%20Singh%20being%20garlanded%20and%20feted%20%E2%80%93%20making%20clear%20there%20was%20no%20real%20change%20of%20guard.%20Medallist%20Sakshi%20Malik%20retired%20from%20wrestling%2C%20gold%20med